# This is a mere example of how env variables are handled in local environments.  
# Do not commit real API keys to git.
#
# Groq:         https://console.groq.com/keys
# Ollama Cloud: https://ollama.com/settings/keys
# Reddit needs no key - it's read via public RSS feeds.
GROQ_API_KEY=
OLLAMA_API_KEY=

# --- Weekly PDF digest -> Google Drive (one-time setup) ---
# Default method is OAuth (works with a personal Gmail). Steps:
# 1. Google Cloud Console: create a project, enable the Drive API.
# 2. Configure the OAuth consent screen (External). Add yourself as a test
#    user, or set it to "In production" so the refresh token doesn't expire
#    every 7 days. The drive.file scope is non-sensitive, so no verification.
# 3. Create an OAuth client of type "Desktop app". Then EITHER download its
#    JSON and set GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_FILE to that path, OR just paste the
#    client id + secret it shows you into GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID / _SECRET.
# 4. In Google Drive, create/pick a folder; copy its id from the folder URL
#    (drive.google.com/drive/folders/<THIS_ID>) into GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID.
# 5. Run once:  poetry run python authorize_drive.py  (browser -> writes token)
GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN_FILE=
GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=
# --- client: use the file OR the id+secret pair (not both needed) ---
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_FILE=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Service-account method (Google Workspace + a Shared Drive only). Set
# report.google_drive.method: service_account in config.yaml to use this.
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_FILE=
